    • Defined in src/runtime/storage/pouchdb/pouch-db-upsert.ts:41

    Provides a way to read-modify-write data for a given PouchDB key based on the following rules:

    • A new entry based on defaultValue is stored if it doesn't exist.
    • If the existing entry is available it is fetched.
    • A copy of the existing document is passed to mutatorFn
    • If the model is new or mutated by mutatorFn, write a new revision.

    Parameters

      The database where we send our get/put calls.

    • docId: string

      The value to get and set

    • Optional mutatorFn: UpsertMutatorFn<T>

      A function that can optionally make changes to the existing entry.

    • Optional defaultValue: PouchDB.Core.NewDocument<T>

      If the docId does not exist use this and also pass through mutatorFn.

    Returns Promise<T>

    the current value of data for docId
